docs.lead_paragraph: The fact that the National holiday, Fourth of July, was celebrated at Princeton over half a century ago will probably be news even to many of the graduates of that university. The Fourth comes now nearly three weeks after the students have gone to their homes for the Summer vacation and its celebration is confined to the residents of Princeton and the denizens of "Dogtown."

headline.main: OLD PRINCETON PRANKS.; How the Students Celebrated the Fourth in 1841.
